WEBVTT

00:01.368 --> 00:03.135
I'm Letty.
- Javier.

00:03.137 --> 00:04.436
There's a man
coming here to kill you.

00:04.438 --> 00:06.372
- You're not an English teacher.
- No.

00:07.207 --> 00:08.507
You work for me now.

00:08.509 --> 00:10.476
I'm not your fucking prisoner!

00:10.478 --> 00:12.845
I need you to be my wife.

00:12.847 --> 00:14.980
Is that your husband?

00:14.982 --> 00:15.981
Uh-huh.

00:15.983 --> 00:18.317
He's talking to my husband.

00:18.319 --> 00:20.219
- You don't have to kill him.
- I do.

00:20.221 --> 00:21.720
Right now.
Let's get out of here.

00:21.722 --> 00:23.022
Bill?

00:23.024 --> 00:24.123
Robin, wait.

00:24.125 --> 00:25.524
Aah!

00:25.526 --> 00:27.159
Javier: We have to put
the bodies in the trunk.

00:27.161 --> 00:29.294
[ Trunk closes ]

00:30.663 --> 00:32.331
♪♪

00:32.333 --> 00:35.868
Woman on recording:
<i>I know that it's okay</i>
<i>to ask for help.</i>

00:37.170 --> 00:41.306
<i>I am calm</i>
<i>in the face of conflict.</i>

00:41.308 --> 00:43.575
<i>I know that my path</i>
<i>has been unique,</i>

00:43.577 --> 00:46.145
<i>and I am grateful for that.</i>

00:46.147 --> 00:47.679
[ Scoffs ]

00:47.681 --> 00:49.481
Javier: Is this
a friend of yours?

00:49.483 --> 00:53.018
Who?
<i>I am right where I need</i>
<i>to be right now.</i>

00:53.020 --> 00:54.520
This woman who talks to you.

00:54.522 --> 00:57.556
In a way.
She's an app.

00:57.558 --> 01:01.060
<i>I am the creator</i>
<i>of my own reality.</i>

01:01.062 --> 01:02.494
How does she know you so well?

01:02.496 --> 01:05.264
<i>I don't blame others</i>
<i>for where I am.</i>

01:05.266 --> 01:06.698
I had nothing to do with this.

01:06.700 --> 01:08.367
You are riding in a car
with three people,

01:08.369 --> 01:09.835
and two of them
are in the trunk.

01:09.837 --> 01:11.203
I didn't kill them.

01:11.205 --> 01:12.871
<i>I choose to be</i>
<i>the type of person...</i>

01:12.873 --> 01:14.173
I only killed one of them.

01:14.175 --> 01:15.407
She was your fault,
and you helped me

01:15.409 --> 01:16.875
put both of them in the trunk,

01:16.877 --> 01:18.718
so you will help me
take them out of the trunk.

01:20.246 --> 01:21.613
No, no, no, no, no,
no, no, no, no.

01:21.615 --> 01:22.948
You're not smoking in this car.

01:22.950 --> 01:24.283
Then let me out of this car.

01:24.285 --> 01:27.519
You don't need me here!
You don't need my help!

01:27.521 --> 01:30.189
Why can't you let me leave,
and we're done?

01:30.191 --> 01:32.424
[ Tires screech ]

01:33.359 --> 01:37.729
To be crystal clear,
I do need you here.

01:37.731 --> 01:39.565
I need your silence.

01:39.567 --> 01:41.400
I need you in my sight
until it's done.

01:41.402 --> 01:43.302
Do you understand?

01:44.204 --> 01:46.805
Do you understand?

01:47.740 --> 01:49.374
Sure.

01:56.816 --> 01:58.250
So, what?

01:58.252 --> 02:00.052
You're gonna just dump them
in a river or something?

02:00.054 --> 02:01.787
Or something.

02:01.789 --> 02:04.756
Something where?

02:04.758 --> 02:05.791
Charleston.

02:05.793 --> 02:07.259
Charleston.

02:07.261 --> 02:09.261
Charleston's very far away.

02:09.263 --> 02:12.231
6 hours.
- 5 1/2 if we make good time.

02:12.233 --> 02:13.832
We'll need to find
a charging station.

02:13.834 --> 02:15.467
We<i> will</i> find
a charging station.

02:15.469 --> 02:17.402
I think that the touchscreen
has a program

02:17.404 --> 02:18.937
that tells you where they are.

02:18.939 --> 02:21.140
Great.
- Oh, shit.

02:21.142 --> 02:22.274
We can't use it.

02:22.276 --> 02:23.509
They disabled the nav system

02:23.511 --> 02:25.777
so that they cannot track
the car.

02:25.779 --> 02:26.645
Awesome.

02:26.647 --> 02:29.281
It's fine.
There are apps.

02:29.283 --> 02:31.316
Like your friend,
- But for charging stations.

02:31.318 --> 02:33.519
We'll download an app.

02:33.521 --> 02:36.688
♪♪

02:38.491 --> 02:40.359
What's in Charles...

02:40.361 --> 02:42.194
Never mind.
I don't even want to know.

02:42.196 --> 02:43.195
Good.

02:43.197 --> 02:45.364
I wasn't gonna tell you.

02:46.866 --> 02:49.701
And then I can go?

02:51.971 --> 02:53.605
Yes.

02:55.475 --> 02:58.143
♪ Hard time forgiving ♪

02:58.145 --> 03:00.712
♪ Even harder forgetting ♪

03:00.714 --> 03:03.115
♪ Before you do something ♪

03:03.117 --> 03:05.484
♪ You might regret, friend ♪

03:05.486 --> 03:08.320
♪ Bricks are caving in ♪

03:08.322 --> 03:10.489
♪ Oh, how sweet this sin ♪

03:10.491 --> 03:13.325
♪ I left you the keys ♪

03:13.327 --> 03:15.494
♪ You won't let me in ♪

03:15.496 --> 03:18.130
♪ Hard time forgiving ♪

03:18.132 --> 03:20.666
♪ Even harder forgetting ♪

03:20.668 --> 03:23.168
♪ Before you do something ♪

03:23.170 --> 03:26.738
♪ You might regret, friend ♪

03:27.740 --> 03:33.145
Okay, so in standard mode,
an 80% charge gets us 216 miles.

03:33.147 --> 03:34.680
How many miles do we have left?

03:34.682 --> 03:36.548
153.

03:36.550 --> 03:42.054
And it's 322 miles
to Charleston, so...

03:44.090 --> 03:46.024
Oh, this is like an SAT thing.

03:46.026 --> 03:48.160
Did you take the SATs?

03:48.162 --> 03:49.895
Yeah.

03:49.897 --> 03:51.697
I thought you dropped out
of high school.

03:51.699 --> 03:54.066
I did.

03:54.068 --> 03:55.867
I did the SATs later.

03:55.869 --> 03:57.002
Like four years ago.

03:57.004 --> 04:00.005
A practice one
- At a Barnes & Noble one day.

04:00.007 --> 04:01.340
I did pretty well.

04:01.342 --> 04:02.941
But not at math.

04:02.943 --> 04:05.244
No, asshole.
Not in math.

04:05.246 --> 04:06.445
In English.

04:06.447 --> 04:08.614
So if you ever want lessons,
let me know.

04:09.549 --> 04:11.350
Did you find
a charging station?

04:11.352 --> 04:13.051
No.

04:13.053 --> 04:16.288
I was downloading the app,
and I just lost service.

04:19.559 --> 04:21.526
Holy shit.
- What?

04:21.528 --> 04:24.463
There's a thing
called Ludicrous Mode.

04:28.568 --> 04:30.802
You are not touching
anything in this car.

04:32.071 --> 04:34.539
Can I...
- No.

04:34.541 --> 04:37.909
Have you hosted
or gambled on cock fights

04:37.911 --> 04:39.878
at any point this week?

04:42.215 --> 04:44.916
[ Sighs ]

04:44.918 --> 04:47.085
Simple, Gary...
all you have to do

04:47.087 --> 04:49.054
to stay out of jail
for the rest of your life

04:49.056 --> 04:51.156
is not go near cock fights.

04:51.158 --> 04:53.925
Yes.

04:53.927 --> 04:57.296
Yes, you understand, or yes,
you've gambled on cock fights?

04:57.298 --> 04:58.563
What?

04:58.565 --> 05:01.433
Get out of here, Gary.

05:01.435 --> 05:03.702
[ Sighs ]

05:05.138 --> 05:06.605
[ Door opens ]

05:06.607 --> 05:08.573
[ Christian sighs ]

05:08.575 --> 05:10.809
[ Door closes ]

05:16.916 --> 05:19.084
[ Dialing ]

05:21.287 --> 05:23.488
[ Ringing ]

05:23.490 --> 05:25.624
- Hi, Letty...
<i>- Your call has been forwarded</i>

05:25.626 --> 05:27.259
<i>to an automatic</i>
<i>voice message system.</i>

05:27.261 --> 05:28.260
[ Sighs ]

05:28.262 --> 05:31.129
Christian.

05:31.131 --> 05:32.698
Yes, Todd.
- Hi.

05:32.700 --> 05:33.498
Hi.

05:33.500 --> 05:35.200
Your office is so great.

05:35.202 --> 05:36.468
[ Sighs ] Thank you.

05:36.470 --> 05:37.502
Every time.

05:37.504 --> 05:38.870
Been this way for six years.

05:38.872 --> 05:40.539
Except for Jacinda
in accounting,

05:40.541 --> 05:42.107
you've been here the longest.

05:42.109 --> 05:43.709
A lot of turnover.

05:43.711 --> 05:46.345
Hope that changes.
- I'm trying to make that change.

05:46.347 --> 05:47.979
Yeah.
I got your manifesto.

05:47.981 --> 05:48.880
Oh, good.

05:48.882 --> 05:50.682
It's around here somewhere.

05:50.684 --> 05:52.884
Still, you deserve
the biggest office.

05:52.886 --> 05:54.686
You could run laps in here.

05:54.688 --> 05:56.488
What can I do for you, Todd?

05:56.490 --> 05:57.723
Nothing.
Nothing.

05:57.725 --> 06:00.659
I was just, um...
[ Clears throat ]

06:00.661 --> 06:02.494
Aren't you supposed to be
in a check-in right now?

06:02.496 --> 06:04.062
No.
- It says at 11:30,

06:04.064 --> 06:05.464
you've got a check-in
with Leticia Raines.

06:05.466 --> 06:07.366
I saw Letty this morning.

06:07.368 --> 06:09.201
She came in early at 7:00.

06:09.203 --> 06:10.202
Letty?

06:10.204 --> 06:11.803
What she goes by.

06:11.805 --> 06:13.038
Huh.

06:13.040 --> 06:14.406
What?

06:14.408 --> 06:16.174
Hmm?
Nothing.

06:16.176 --> 06:18.510
It's nice to have that
familiarity with your parolees,

06:18.512 --> 06:19.845
but don't get too close, right?

06:19.847 --> 06:21.847
Because I know
why I wanted this career,

06:21.849 --> 06:23.915
which I'm sure
is the same for you.

06:23.917 --> 06:26.084
You seem sure.

06:28.488 --> 06:29.921
I have to make
some phone calls.

06:29.923 --> 06:31.656
Good.

06:31.658 --> 06:35.427
Love this office.
Every time.

06:39.098 --> 06:41.566
Letty: How long before we run
out of juice?

06:41.568 --> 06:43.201
Javier: 122 miles.

06:43.203 --> 06:45.070
121.

06:45.072 --> 06:47.773
♪♪

06:48.908 --> 06:52.544
You know they're already
looking for this car.

06:52.546 --> 06:53.712
No, not yet.

06:53.714 --> 06:55.480
Check-out is at 11:00.

07:03.890 --> 07:06.825
[ Object clacks ]

07:09.862 --> 07:12.130
Javier:
Do you have service?

07:13.466 --> 07:15.167
No.

07:17.870 --> 07:20.505
[ Sighs ]

07:44.831 --> 07:47.399
Javier: Switch it
to Airplane Mode and off.

07:47.401 --> 07:49.968
Letty:
- You say that like you didn't
say it five minutes ago,

07:49.970 --> 07:52.304
like I haven't tried that
five times.

07:52.306 --> 07:54.139
Try again.

07:54.141 --> 07:56.575
[ Sighs ]

07:57.443 --> 07:59.644
Oh. Okay.
- What?

07:59.646 --> 08:01.913
I have three bars.
It's downloading.

08:01.915 --> 08:03.181
Good.

08:03.183 --> 08:05.016
It's taking forever.

08:05.018 --> 08:07.118
Woman:
<i>Welcome to Carolina Fish Fry.</i>

08:07.120 --> 08:08.787
<i>Can I take your order?</i>
Yeah.

08:08.789 --> 08:11.656
I'm gonna have the flounder
and shrimp combo platter

08:11.658 --> 08:13.758
with hush puppies
and a Dr Pepper.

08:13.760 --> 08:14.926
What do you want?

08:14.928 --> 08:16.962
I'm sorry, I just need to...

08:16.964 --> 08:18.697
[ Grunts ]

08:18.699 --> 08:21.066
So many things.
How am I gonna choose?

08:22.101 --> 08:23.869
I wouldn't take you
for indecisive.

08:23.871 --> 08:25.937
I'm not except with food.

08:25.939 --> 08:28.807
Okay.
Fried deviled crab?

08:28.809 --> 08:31.009
That could either way.

08:31.011 --> 08:32.110
Okay, I'm gonna have

08:32.112 --> 08:34.646
the flounder and shrimp
combo platter, also,

08:34.648 --> 08:37.549
but I want mine with fries
and a Diet Coke.

08:37.551 --> 08:38.984
<i>Since you're getting</i>
<i>the same thing,</i>

08:38.986 --> 08:40.519
<i>do you want to do</i>
<i>the family bucket?</i>

08:40.521 --> 08:41.653
How much is it?

08:41.655 --> 08:43.288
<i>$28.99.</i>

08:43.290 --> 08:44.656
$28.99?

08:44.658 --> 08:46.892
Does it come
with a lottery ticket?

08:50.863 --> 08:53.398
We'll just stick
- With our separate orders.

08:53.400 --> 08:56.635
<i>Please drive around</i>
<i>to the first window.</i>

08:56.637 --> 08:58.236
[ Cellphone chimes ]

08:59.906 --> 09:03.975
Letty: Okay, there's a charging
station in 31 miles.

09:03.977 --> 09:05.010
Javier: Good.

09:05.012 --> 09:07.345
But it takes us
- 10 miles out of our way.

09:07.347 --> 09:09.180
Of course it does.

09:09.182 --> 09:10.749
[ Sighs ]

09:15.488 --> 09:17.188
You're near-sighted.

09:17.190 --> 09:18.189
What?

09:18.191 --> 09:20.191
You need glasses
to see far away.

09:20.193 --> 09:22.327
Oh.
Not really.

09:24.730 --> 09:27.098
Here.
Try these.

09:36.409 --> 09:39.010
Wow.
- What does that sign say?

09:39.012 --> 09:42.113
"Try the new anus pounder."

09:42.115 --> 09:44.816
[ Both laugh ]

09:50.723 --> 09:53.625
[ Clears throat ]

09:54.360 --> 09:57.028
- Yeah. [ Clears throat ]
- There you go.

09:59.699 --> 10:03.435
Have a good day.

10:06.772 --> 10:09.074
Oh, I can't eat this.

10:09.076 --> 10:10.976
You have to eat.
- It smells.

10:10.978 --> 10:13.345
It's the food.
It's the bodies.

10:14.981 --> 10:17.882
♪♪

10:27.093 --> 10:29.060
[ Thud ]

10:30.496 --> 10:31.496
Shit.

10:31.498 --> 10:33.798
You okay?
- Yeah.

10:35.167 --> 10:38.403
Oh, my God.
Are you okay?

10:38.405 --> 10:39.838
Oh, my gosh.
I'm sorry.

10:39.840 --> 10:41.106
I'm so sorry.
I...

10:41.108 --> 10:43.174
My kids are just driving me...

10:43.176 --> 10:45.377
They're not driving, obviously.

10:47.313 --> 10:48.813
Oh, my gosh.

10:48.815 --> 10:52.417
I think we should exchange
insurance cards and information.
No.

10:52.419 --> 10:54.653
I definitely think we should,
'cause you never know.

10:54.655 --> 10:57.355
It's not necessary.
- Well...

10:57.357 --> 10:59.157
You stopped pretty abruptly.

10:59.159 --> 11:01.159
- What are you talking about?
- At the light.

11:01.161 --> 11:03.261
You came to a screeching halt.

11:03.263 --> 11:04.462
You're joking.

11:04.464 --> 11:05.964
It was very out of the blue.

11:05.966 --> 11:07.365
I was already stopped.

11:07.367 --> 11:09.200
Oh, I don't think so.

11:09.202 --> 11:11.369
Okay.

11:11.371 --> 11:14.105
It doesn't matter what you think
'cause you were behind me.

11:14.107 --> 11:15.473
So it's your responsibility.

11:15.475 --> 11:17.308
I think that maybe we should
call the cops, actually.

11:17.310 --> 11:19.611
It would be much better for you
if we don't call the cops.

11:19.613 --> 11:21.146
No, no.
- My husband would want me to.

11:21.148 --> 11:22.547
Yeah, well, it was your fault.

11:22.549 --> 11:24.649
Then I'll just call them.
Your car is fine, right?

11:24.651 --> 11:26.051
[ Scoffs ] I don't know.

11:26.053 --> 11:28.119
Yes, your car is fine.
Yeah, but yours isn't.

11:28.121 --> 11:29.988
I mean, look at your trunk.
It doesn't even...
- I'll fix it.

11:29.990 --> 11:31.222
You don't need to.
Okay, look.

11:31.224 --> 11:32.857
I think that we should
exchange information

11:32.859 --> 11:34.325
and get a policeman
- To write up a little thing.

11:34.327 --> 11:35.960
That way,
there is no disagreements

11:35.962 --> 11:37.829
and then no one's
- Coming after each other later

11:37.831 --> 11:39.497
because this happened to me
once before.

11:39.499 --> 11:40.965
I'm sure it did.

11:40.967 --> 11:43.401
And I didn't get any insurance
information or anything,

11:43.403 --> 11:44.836
and my husband just...

11:44.838 --> 11:47.172
This is supposed to recognize
your thumbprint, but...

11:47.174 --> 11:49.074
- Are you gonna sue them, Mom?
- Stay in the car, Bryce.

11:49.076 --> 11:51.309
- Your trunk is broken.
- Mommy is handling this!

11:51.311 --> 11:52.844
Stay in the car.

11:52.846 --> 11:54.079
I need to take a picture
of your license plate.

11:54.081 --> 11:56.214
Excuse me.
- You don't need to.

11:56.882 --> 11:58.249
Excuse me.

11:58.251 --> 12:00.819
Babe, I think we need
to head to the hospital.

12:01.520 --> 12:02.854
- Oh, God.
- Yeah.

12:02.856 --> 12:04.389
Something doesn't feel right.

12:04.391 --> 12:05.690
I think I might be...

12:05.692 --> 12:07.525
She was kicking,
but now she's not.

12:07.527 --> 12:09.728
Oh, my God.
Uh...

12:09.730 --> 12:11.596
Go.
- You need to go to the hospital.

12:11.598 --> 12:13.164
I'm Melanie, by the way.

12:13.166 --> 12:14.532
Do you want me
to call you somebody?
An ambulance, or...?

12:14.534 --> 12:16.201
No, I think we'll get there
faster if we just...

12:16.203 --> 12:17.936
Right.
If you just go. Now.

12:17.938 --> 12:19.738
But if there was damage
to your car...

12:19.740 --> 12:21.039
I don't think
that there was any damage.

12:21.041 --> 12:23.108
- Mom!
- Shut the hell up, Bryce!

12:23.110 --> 12:25.110
I'm so sorry. Go. Go.
There's no damage.

12:25.112 --> 12:26.911
Great.
Thanks.

12:28.547 --> 12:29.948
Oh.

12:30.916 --> 12:32.183
Javier: There.
- Go.

12:32.185 --> 12:33.952
What did you just push?
- Go.

12:33.954 --> 12:35.920
- Whoa!
- Holy shit!

12:35.922 --> 12:38.857
[ Tires squeal ]

12:42.394 --> 12:44.229
Wow.

12:44.231 --> 12:47.198
Wow!

12:47.200 --> 12:49.467
[ Sighs ]

12:53.739 --> 12:56.207
[ Trunk lid clacking ]

12:58.577 --> 13:00.645
You got to tie that thing down
or something.

13:00.647 --> 13:01.880
It's bouncing.

13:01.882 --> 13:03.581
When we get
to the charging station.

13:03.583 --> 13:04.883
How much further?

13:04.885 --> 13:08.019
6 miles on the right
in a gas station.

13:10.790 --> 13:13.491
[ Bag rustling ]

13:16.262 --> 13:20.131
How can we be down to 19?
We were at 51 at the fish place.

13:22.802 --> 13:24.903
Well, I'm sure it had something
to do with your Ludicrous Mode.

13:24.905 --> 13:26.404
My Ludicrous Mode?

13:26.406 --> 13:28.273
Yeah.
- It probably ate up the battery.

13:28.275 --> 13:29.774
Are you saying I shouldn't
have pushed that button?

13:29.776 --> 13:32.443
I'm just saying it's why
the battery ran out faster.

13:32.445 --> 13:33.645
That bitch was trying

13:33.647 --> 13:35.847
to take a picture of our plates
when we drove off.

13:35.849 --> 13:37.182
We would have been
totally screwed

13:37.184 --> 13:39.017
as soon as they put out
an APB on this thing.

13:39.019 --> 13:40.785
We should have
- Just driven away normally.

13:40.787 --> 13:43.321
To a hospital
to save your wife's baby?

13:44.356 --> 13:46.791
Yeah, that was good.

13:46.793 --> 13:48.293
You did good with that.

13:48.295 --> 13:49.928
Yeah, I did good with that.

13:49.930 --> 13:52.430
And I still haven't heard
a thank you, have I?

13:52.432 --> 13:53.598
I guess not.

13:53.600 --> 13:55.466
You were trying to convince
that insane woman

13:55.468 --> 13:56.668
not to call the cops,

13:56.670 --> 13:58.636
which no one without two bodies
in the trunk would do.

13:58.638 --> 14:00.805
They'd be like,
- "No shit we're calling the cops

14:00.807 --> 14:02.540
because you rear-ended
my fucking Tesla."

14:02.542 --> 14:04.542
Shut up.

14:05.878 --> 14:07.345
Don't tell me to shut up.

14:07.347 --> 14:11.182
Don't<i> ever</i> tell me to shut up.

