20:02.467 --> 20:05.069
[ Knock on door ]
Man: Ma'am?

20:05.071 --> 20:07.004
Just a minute.

20:07.006 --> 20:10.708
♪♪

20:18.350 --> 20:21.485
Sorry. I just unlocked
the next level on "Mister Jump."

20:21.487 --> 20:23.020
Congrats.

20:23.022 --> 20:24.255
Thanks.

20:24.257 --> 20:26.157
I've never played
that one before.

20:26.159 --> 20:27.491
It's addictive.

20:27.493 --> 20:30.761
Well, your boyfriend
or whatever is out there,

20:30.763 --> 20:34.332
and I wanted to go put this sign
on the charging station,

20:34.334 --> 20:36.867
but I couldn't
leave you in here alone.

20:36.869 --> 20:38.336
I'm the only one here,

20:38.338 --> 20:40.571
so I can't walk outside
if there's a customer.

20:40.573 --> 20:43.674
You know, just in case of, like,
shoplifting or whatever.

20:43.676 --> 20:46.010
- So the charger doesn't work?
- It's a real piece of shit.

20:46.012 --> 20:49.247
It likes to work, I don't know,
once every two weeks or so.

20:49.249 --> 20:52.116
Tried to tell
- The jackass who installed it,

20:52.118 --> 20:53.751
but he was just like,
"What?"

20:53.753 --> 20:55.586
Do you know if the next
station is close by?

20:55.588 --> 20:58.422
Um, there's one in Greenville.

20:58.424 --> 21:01.259
And I think it's actually
a supercharger station.

21:01.261 --> 21:03.628
Like, the one
- That's meant for your car.

21:03.630 --> 21:05.730
Should give you
- A full charge in like...

21:05.732 --> 21:07.064
An hour.
I know.

21:07.066 --> 21:08.266
How far is it?

21:08.268 --> 21:11.702
To Greenville?
Mm, like 40 miles.

21:11.704 --> 21:13.738
Like 40, 50 miles.

21:13.740 --> 21:15.640
We only have 13 miles left.

21:16.475 --> 21:18.042
Do you have a regular outlet?

21:18.044 --> 21:19.377
It takes forever.

21:19.379 --> 21:20.811
Do you have a 240-volt?

21:20.813 --> 21:23.481
Yeah.
Still takes forever.

21:23.483 --> 21:25.383
If we charge it
for an hour-and-a-half,

21:25.385 --> 21:26.884
it'll get us to Greenville.

21:30.922 --> 21:33.224
[ High-pitched whine ]

21:37.763 --> 21:40.665
[ Muffled ] You got
the cord in your trunk?

21:40.667 --> 21:41.732
What?

21:41.734 --> 21:45.169
The cord should
be in your trunk.

21:57.182 --> 21:58.482
Is there a charging cord
in the trunk?

21:58.484 --> 22:00.084
Where the hell have you been?

22:00.086 --> 22:01.152
Figuring this shit out.

22:01.154 --> 22:02.420
We can charge the car
in an outlet

22:02.422 --> 22:03.988
at the side of the building
right there.

22:03.990 --> 22:05.790
Is there a cord in the trunk?

22:05.792 --> 22:07.325
Yes.

22:07.327 --> 22:08.793
But I just fixed the trunk.

22:08.795 --> 22:10.261
Okay.

22:10.263 --> 22:12.196
The trunk is closed.

22:12.198 --> 22:13.431
I hope not permanently.

22:13.433 --> 22:15.366
No, with duct tape.

22:15.368 --> 22:17.101
Where'd you get duct tape?

22:17.103 --> 22:19.270
I always have duct tape.

22:19.272 --> 22:20.604
Trick of the trade?

22:20.606 --> 22:24.208
It's not a trick.
It's just tape.

22:26.011 --> 22:28.346
[ Door opens ]

22:33.785 --> 22:36.954
[ Tesla chimes ]

22:40.359 --> 22:43.894
There.
That's it, right there.

22:43.896 --> 22:45.796
Okay.

22:45.798 --> 22:48.299
[ Bag rustles]

22:48.301 --> 22:50.634
I'm out.

22:54.139 --> 22:57.174
Don't... Don't smoke
at a gas station.
- Why not?

22:57.176 --> 22:59.410
Why not let the place
go up in flames?

22:59.412 --> 23:02.213
Make this a lot easier.

23:02.215 --> 23:04.548
[ Sighs ] [ Lighter clicks ]

23:04.550 --> 23:07.218
Just tell me
if someone's looking.

23:07.220 --> 23:08.552
I'm looking.

23:09.321 --> 23:11.489
If someone else is looking.

23:11.491 --> 23:13.357
Nobody's looking.

23:13.359 --> 23:15.493
No one cares about you.

23:22.367 --> 23:24.435
[ Grunts ]

23:28.540 --> 23:30.574
[ Trunk lid closes ]

23:36.515 --> 23:37.982
Oh.
Christian.

23:39.618 --> 23:40.584
Yes?

23:40.586 --> 23:42.086
You're the man I'm looking for.

23:42.088 --> 23:43.721
It seems that way.

23:43.723 --> 23:44.522
Ha!

23:44.524 --> 23:46.690
You're always so funny.

23:46.692 --> 23:48.392
Remember how you said
you had a check-in

23:48.394 --> 23:50.027
with that woman
this morning at 7:00?

23:50.029 --> 23:52.263
Letty?
- Right. Letty.

23:52.265 --> 23:54.198
But as I was doing
the time sheets,

23:54.200 --> 23:56.200
I realized you weren't in
at 7:00 a.m.

23:56.202 --> 23:57.735
I don't do time sheets.

23:57.737 --> 23:59.370
Of course not.
I know.

23:59.372 --> 24:01.906
But I was looking
- At everybody else's time sheets,

24:01.908 --> 24:03.874
and I was checking
- On something with Rashida,

24:03.876 --> 24:07.244
and Rashida said you rode the
elevator with her this morning.

24:07.246 --> 24:08.612
Okay.

24:08.614 --> 24:12.049
Meaning you and Rashida
got here at the same time.

24:12.051 --> 24:13.384
At 8:00 A.M.

24:13.386 --> 24:16.887
[ Laughs ]
You're checking up on me?

24:16.889 --> 24:18.556
No, I just couldn't read

24:18.558 --> 24:20.724
Rashida's handwriting
on her time sheet,

24:20.726 --> 24:22.893
so I asked her, and she said

24:22.895 --> 24:24.562
[Imitating Rashida]
"I got here at 8:00 A.M.

24:24.564 --> 24:25.896
And you can ask Christian

24:25.898 --> 24:28.332
'cause we rode
- Up the elevator together."

24:28.334 --> 24:30.734
Are you doing a black voice?

24:33.905 --> 24:35.739
I'm gonna use the bathroom now.

24:35.741 --> 24:38.275
Okay.

24:38.277 --> 24:40.578
[ Door opens ]

24:44.950 --> 24:47.051
♪♪

25:12.777 --> 25:15.779
Javier:
He looks like you.

25:15.781 --> 25:17.515
Don't be a dick.

25:19.117 --> 25:22.853
You have the same eyebrows.

25:24.155 --> 25:25.789
Yeah.

25:27.125 --> 25:29.193
I want to get him back.

25:29.195 --> 25:30.861
I know.

25:32.197 --> 25:34.832
I think you can.

25:34.834 --> 25:36.634
You do?

25:36.636 --> 25:38.135
Yeah.

25:38.137 --> 25:39.870
If you stop screwing up.

25:40.539 --> 25:42.473
I'm trying.

25:42.475 --> 25:44.141
Try harder.

25:44.143 --> 25:46.810
Well, I'm trying real hard
to get away from you.

25:46.812 --> 25:50.047
I think that would be a step in
the right direction, don't you?

25:53.018 --> 25:55.019
Young man: [ Groans ]
Young man ♪2: Come on.

25:55.021 --> 25:56.587
Come on!

25:58.223 --> 25:59.423
We leave now.
- We can't.

25:59.425 --> 26:01.659
It's only been charging
for 15 minutes.

26:01.661 --> 26:02.893
The police will be here.

26:02.895 --> 26:05.396
It needs to charge
for at least an hour.

26:06.531 --> 26:07.698
What you got?
- Hey.

26:07.700 --> 26:09.066
I've already called the cops.

26:09.068 --> 26:10.935
♪♪

26:15.206 --> 26:18.976
[ Young men grunting,
shouting indistinctly ]

26:32.424 --> 26:35.192
Letty:
So, what's the plan?

26:35.194 --> 26:37.561
The charging station
is 40 miles away.

26:37.563 --> 26:38.596
40 or 50.

26:38.598 --> 26:40.264
We'll stop
at the next gas station

26:40.266 --> 26:41.732
and charge it
in a regular outlet.

26:41.734 --> 26:43.701
But if they don't have
a 240-volt,

26:43.703 --> 26:45.235
if it's just a regular plug,

26:45.237 --> 26:47.304
we only get 3 to 4 miles
per hour of charging.

26:47.306 --> 26:49.640
Then we will stop many times.

26:55.046 --> 26:58.949
Can you just please let me go?

27:00.619 --> 27:02.353
No.

27:10.295 --> 27:12.563
[ Sighs ]

27:14.899 --> 27:16.967
There.

27:22.474 --> 27:25.542
[ Keyboard clacking ]

27:32.250 --> 27:35.653
Ah, come on.

27:35.655 --> 27:37.821
How'd you get so good at this?

27:37.823 --> 27:40.124
I'm not so good.
You're just so bad.

27:40.126 --> 27:41.158
[ Laughs ]

27:41.160 --> 27:43.427
[ Telephone rings ]

27:45.030 --> 27:46.263
[ Telephone beeps ]

27:46.265 --> 27:47.364
Hello?

27:47.366 --> 27:48.999
Is this Estelle Raines?

27:49.001 --> 27:50.868
Yes, it is.
Who's this?

27:50.870 --> 27:53.504
I'm your daughter's
parole officer.

27:53.506 --> 27:55.539
Okay.

27:55.541 --> 27:58.008
I can't seem to track her down.

27:58.010 --> 28:01.679
Um, it doesn't mean
anything is terribly wrong.

28:01.681 --> 28:03.180
Sure it does.

28:03.182 --> 28:05.049
I'm sorry?

28:05.051 --> 28:06.850
How well do you know
my daughter?

28:08.520 --> 28:10.688
Any idea where she might be?

28:10.690 --> 28:13.457
[ Sighs ]

28:13.459 --> 28:14.992
Not a clue.

28:14.994 --> 28:16.560
Thank you.

28:18.196 --> 28:20.531
[ Telephone beeps ]

28:23.134 --> 28:25.035
♪♪

28:25.037 --> 28:26.937
Give me my money!

28:29.874 --> 28:32.643
♪♪

28:35.046 --> 28:38.982
[ Thunder rumbles ]

28:38.984 --> 28:40.250
This doesn't look good.

28:40.252 --> 28:42.186
It said gas and food
in five miles.

28:42.188 --> 28:43.587
You saw the same sign I did.

28:43.589 --> 28:45.489
Maybe it was five miles
to the exit

28:45.491 --> 28:47.024
but then the station
was further.

28:47.026 --> 28:49.059
I know as much as you do.

28:50.161 --> 28:52.963
[ Sighs ]

28:55.066 --> 28:57.401
[ Inhales, exhales deeply ]

29:00.538 --> 29:03.907
[ Cellphone rings ]

29:03.909 --> 29:05.342
[ Cellphone beeps ]

29:05.344 --> 29:06.443
Hello?

29:06.445 --> 29:08.545
Hi, there.
I'm looking for Letty.

29:08.547 --> 29:10.481
Letty.
- Yes.

29:12.217 --> 29:14.218
Letty Raines?

29:14.220 --> 29:16.220
Yes.

29:16.222 --> 29:17.588
[ Scoffs ]

29:17.590 --> 29:19.189
I haven't seen her in years.

29:19.191 --> 29:21.091
[ Chuckles ] She still alive?

29:21.093 --> 29:24.428
Hope so. Anyway,
sorry to bother you...
Whoa.
Who the hell is this?

29:24.430 --> 29:25.963
[ Dial tone ]

29:25.965 --> 29:28.332
Woman: [ In distance ]
I thought you were meditating!

29:29.534 --> 29:31.101
I mean, I talked to her
a few weeks ago.

29:31.103 --> 29:33.270
She seemed good, like she was
getting back on her feet.

29:33.272 --> 29:34.571
Is she okay?

29:34.573 --> 29:36.440
Well, that's what
I'm trying to find out.

29:36.442 --> 29:37.775
You're Christian, right?

29:37.777 --> 29:39.376
I mean,
- Not like in the Jesus way.

29:39.378 --> 29:40.778
Like, your name is Christian?

29:40.780 --> 29:41.612
Yes.

29:41.614 --> 29:43.313
Letty told me about you.

29:43.315 --> 29:45.549
She, uh...
she really likes you.

29:45.551 --> 29:47.951
That's nice to hear.

29:47.953 --> 29:49.453
If you talk to her,

29:49.455 --> 29:51.155
will you please tell her
to call me?

29:51.157 --> 29:53.056
For sure.
Yeah.

29:53.058 --> 29:55.058
Thank you.

29:55.060 --> 29:57.161
[ Receiver clacks ]

29:59.798 --> 30:01.865
♪♪

30:03.134 --> 30:04.501
<i>Your call has been forwarded</i>

30:04.503 --> 30:07.704
<i>to an automatic</i>
<i>voice message system.</i>

30:18.249 --> 30:19.449
[ Door closes ]

30:19.451 --> 30:20.984
[ Sighs ]

30:20.986 --> 30:22.152
There.

30:22.154 --> 30:24.521
Get your phone charger
to see if there's power.

30:24.523 --> 30:27.257
Whoa.
Smart.

30:27.259 --> 30:28.759
Thank you.

30:33.031 --> 30:35.566
[ Thunder rumbles ]

30:42.507 --> 30:44.608
No juice.

30:46.277 --> 30:48.078
Oh, my gosh.

30:53.117 --> 30:56.220
Can we just bury the bodies
out here somewhere?

30:56.222 --> 30:57.988
We?
- No. You.

30:57.990 --> 30:59.122
Obviously, you.

30:59.124 --> 31:00.324
No one will see...

31:00.326 --> 31:01.458
I can't believe
I'm saying this.

31:01.460 --> 31:04.995
Yeah, me neither.
Stop talking.

31:04.997 --> 31:06.597
What is in Charleston?

31:08.132 --> 31:10.200
No, if I'm here with you,
if I'm part of this,

31:10.202 --> 31:12.836
I want to know why we have to go
all the way to Charleston

31:12.838 --> 31:14.738
when this could have been over.

31:16.407 --> 31:18.809
Tell me.

31:20.578 --> 31:22.913
[ Sighs ]

31:27.552 --> 31:29.586
When I was young,
watching movies,

31:29.588 --> 31:32.189
I always thought
it was so stupid

31:32.191 --> 31:34.925
when they dump a body
in the river or a lake

31:34.927 --> 31:37.694
or dug a hole in the ground.

31:37.696 --> 31:40.497
The body still exists.
It will be found.

31:40.499 --> 31:42.566
The killer will be found
eventually.

31:42.568 --> 31:47.471
A body must disappear
completely.

31:48.506 --> 31:50.040
I thought...

31:50.042 --> 31:52.976
Why don't they make a friend
at a funeral home...

31:55.780 --> 31:58.015
and cremate the body?

31:58.017 --> 32:00.684
♪♪

32:01.552 --> 32:03.587
Because you have to trust
that person.

32:06.858 --> 32:08.425
Yes.

32:08.427 --> 32:10.794
You do.

32:17.235 --> 32:19.503
[ Sighs ]

32:33.484 --> 32:36.153
[ Console chimes ]

32:36.155 --> 32:39.423
There's no way we're going to
make it, so what is your plan?

32:39.425 --> 32:41.024
[ Console chimes ]

32:44.896 --> 32:47.130
I think we're stopping here.

32:47.132 --> 32:49.833
[ Thunder rumbles ]

32:55.273 --> 32:57.541
[ Insects chirping ]

33:02.480 --> 33:04.514
Do you have service?

33:04.516 --> 33:08.118
No. You?

33:08.120 --> 33:10.554
No.

33:23.101 --> 33:25.135
So, that was it?

33:25.137 --> 33:26.870
You watched movies as a kid

33:26.872 --> 33:29.339
and thought you'd do
a better job at killing people

33:29.341 --> 33:30.474
and getting away with it?

33:30.476 --> 33:31.541
No.

33:31.543 --> 33:33.210
[ Thunder rumbles ]

33:33.212 --> 33:37.080
So, how did you get
into this esteemed profession?

33:47.692 --> 33:50.160
Maybe I'll tell you one day.

33:50.162 --> 33:53.330
One day?
- This is the one day you got.

33:53.332 --> 33:56.400
There might be more days.

33:58.836 --> 34:01.104
I really hope not.

34:01.806 --> 34:04.408
This is what I'm good at.

34:04.410 --> 34:06.376
[ Scoffs ]

34:06.378 --> 34:09.379
Yeah.
You're doing just great.

34:09.381 --> 34:10.747
[ Chuckles ]

34:10.749 --> 34:12.482
Everything would have
been just fine

34:12.484 --> 34:14.184
if you hadn't messed it all up.

34:14.186 --> 34:16.553
- You must be joking.
- Not at all.

34:16.555 --> 34:18.855
Letty: I didn't want
to mess it all up.

34:18.857 --> 34:20.724
I didn't want to be involved
in this at all.

34:20.726 --> 34:22.526
You got involved
when you decided

34:22.528 --> 34:25.729
to steal from my hotel room,
when you hid in my closet,

34:25.731 --> 34:27.764
when you followed me,
when you slept with me,

34:27.766 --> 34:29.266
when you lied,
when you took my money!

34:29.268 --> 34:30.434
Bullshit!

34:30.436 --> 34:32.235
You didn't have to kidnap me
from a hotel room

34:32.237 --> 34:34.337
and force me
to be your accomplice!

34:34.339 --> 34:36.907
I saved your life!
- Why?

34:40.044 --> 34:41.545
I don't know.

34:41.547 --> 34:43.713
Well, thank you, my prince.

34:43.715 --> 34:46.183
I'm so glad
to be alive right now.

34:46.185 --> 34:47.951
All alone
- In the middle of nowhere

34:47.953 --> 34:50.120
with a murderer,
two dead bodies,
and no way out.

34:50.122 --> 34:53.290
I can't thank you enough
for rescuing me.

35:07.705 --> 35:09.339
I am sorry.

35:11.275 --> 35:12.776
